Centralism
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the name for the point of view, or the movement, which supported the absolute authority of the central General General Assembly over the several Provincial Councils: with Vogel's abolition of provincial Governments in 187?, the word became unnecessary and dropped out of use contrast Provincialism
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
