Quote: After all, the names `Centralist' and `Provincialist' do not in most cases give a truer impression than party nick-names generally convey. `Centralism', properly so called, is repugnant to all the political instincts of Englishmen. `Provincialism' is as repugnant their educated sympat who are called or erroneously call themselves Centralists are truer friends of local self-government than many of the defenders of `Provincialism', ..
